  "texts": [
    "The residual is evaluated at a set of N N points, called collocation points.",
    "Taking the mean squared error over the residual evaluations yields the PDE lossL N = 1 2N N N N i=1 ||N [u(x i); λ(x i)]|| 2 2 = 1 2N N N N i=1 d dx E A(x i) du(x i) dx + p(x i) 2.",
    "(30)The gradients of the possible predictions, i.e., u, E A, and p with respect to x, are obtained with automatic differentiation [51] through the NN approximation.",
    "Similarly, the boundary conditions are enforced at the N B D + N B N boundary points.L B = 1 2N N D N B D i=1 (u(x i) -g) 2 + 1 2N B N N B N i=1 E A(x i) du(x i) dx -f 2 (31)The cost function is composed of the PDE loss L N, boundary loss L B, and possibly a data-driven lossL D C = L N + L B + L D. (32)Both the deep least-squares method [235] and the deep Galerkin method [236] are closely related.",
    "Instead of focusing on the residuals at individual collocation points as in PINNs, these methods consider the L 2 -norm of the residuals integrated over the domain."
